Durban - Staff at an Overport supermarket were held at gunpoint and robbed of their cellphones on Monday.  A video of the incident at the Checkmart has gone viral on social media. In the footage of the incident, two men can be seen walking into the store. The first man has a firearm in his hand and walks towards three people, who are believed to be staff members.  A second man follows him and then is seen collecting cellphones from the three. Later in the video, other men are seen entering the store.   Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said officers had responded to the incident.  “It is alleged by the complainant that on February 21, 2022 at about 6.10am he was at the shop with his employees in Hill Street in Sydenham when six armed men entered the shop and demanded their cell phones and money,” she said. Mbele added that the complainant pressed the panic button and the suspects fled the scene with cell phones.  “No one was injured and a case of robbery was opened at Mayville SAPS for investigation,” she said. Zain Sooiswala from eThekwini Secure said the suspects were believed to have fled the scene in a silver Polo Vivo and white Toyota Hilux. The incident was confirmed by Checkmart head office which said that no injuries were reported. According to the latest crime statistics released by Police Minister Bheki Cele last Friday, there was a 7.9% decrease in the number of business robbery cases reported to the police in KZN in the period October to December 2021 compared with the previous period.  THE MERCURY